critique: This executive order primarily deals with the regulation of aerial flights for military personnel and officers of the Public Health Service detailed with the Coast Guard. It outlines who is required to participate in these flights and who can authorize such requirements. It also amends previous orders to include officers of the Public Health Service detailed for duty with the Coast Guard. There's no indication of ideological bias, immigration policy changes, expansion of executive power, or shifts in federalism. The order seems neutral regarding national security vs. civil liberties, economic regulation, and social inclusion. Therefore, all scores are set to 0.
